properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 3:36PM AKST until January 13 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Travel will be
difficult. Areas of poor visibility are expected. Additional
snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches, are expected.

* WHERE...Baldwin Peninsula and Selawik Valley.

* WHEN...6 PM Sunday to noon Monday. Falling snow will develop
late Sunday and continue into Monday. The lowest visibility will
be Sunday night through Monday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong winds are occuring tonight and
will continue into Monday. Falling snow will develop late
Sunday and continue into Monday. The lowest visibility will be
Sunday through Monday.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM SUNDAY TO NOON AKST MONDAY
